\begin_layout Section
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Loan Rules
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 Menu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
This is a facility to define lending rules based on the Member Type, Collection
 Type and GMD.
 The rules set out in this facility are: Limit number of loan items (Loan
 Limit), the period of the loan (Loan Period), Limit loan extensions (Reborrow
 Limit), the penalty per day overdue (Fine Each Day), and overdue tolerance
 (Overdue Grace Period)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
\align center
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename ../SLiMS-5-En-Documentation/image/sirk-loanrules.png
	scale 35

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\lang bahasa
Loan Rules 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
An example of defining Loan Rules:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
In the library you have 3 types of collections: books, audiovisual (AV)
 and theses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
One type of membership your library has is : Student loans, with a total
 allowance of 2 items, namely: one item from the book collection and one
 more from the AV collection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For that you would need to create the membership type: "Students" , with
 total borrowing from two collections.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
So, in Loan Rules this must be defined:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Member type "Student", borrowing allowance for collection="Book" is 1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Member type "Student", borrowing allowance for collection="AV" is 1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Member type "Student", borrowing allowance for collection="Thesis" is 0.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Quote
Everything must be defined, otherwise it can be exceeded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Loan History
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 Menu
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quote
Contains data of every transaction ever undertaken.
 Resulting data comprises: Member ID, Member Name, Item Code, Title, Loan
 date, Due date.
 In this menu the facility is also provided to print a list of borrowing
 history.
 In addition it is also possible to perform a search of history data.
 History data search can be done by Member ID/Member Name, Document Title,
 Item Code, Date From and Loan Loan Until Date.
 This facility can be displayed by clicking the Show More Filter Options.
\end_layout

